The following command installs the .NET HTTP REPL command-line tool that you'll use to make HTTP requests to the web API.

    dotnet tool install -g Microsoft.dotnet-httprepl

Connect to the web API by running the following command

    httprepl https://localhost:{PORT}

Explore available endpoints by running the following command - detects all APIs available on the connected endpoint.

    ls

Go to an endpoint by running the following command - shows an output of available APIs for the endpoint

    cd NAME_ENDPOINT

Exit

    exit


